[SN]TITLE[SN]
West Ham hamper fraud: Trial rescheduled for October

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The trial of a man accused of a Christmas hamper con which saw West Ham players lose thousands of pounds has been abandoned.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Stephen Ackerman, 48, of Loughton, Essex, denies 19 fraud charges with the proceeds totalling more than Â£60,000.
Mr Ackerman is accused of selling hampers to players that never arrived under the alias Mark Kingston.
The jury has been discharged with a new trial set to start on 24 October at Snaresbrook Crown Court.
